## 7. Conclusion
### 7.1 Summary
This project successfully demonstrates an AI-based approach to detecting phishing URLs embedded in QR codes. The system achieves 95% accuracy using a Random Forest classifier with 12 URL-based features.
### 7.2 Key Achievements
- Developed end-to-end QR code analysis pipeline
- Implemented robust feature extraction
- Trained effective ML model
- Created user-friendly CLI interface
### 7.3 Limitations
- Dataset size is limited (100 samples)
- Does not analyze webpage content
- Cannot detect zero-day phishing sites
- Relies on URL patterns only
### 7.4 Future Scope
- Expand dataset with more samples
